# amctl Project Rules

## Overview

amctl is an Android device remote control solution exposing MCP protocol tools for AI agents.

- **v1** (complete): Accessibility Service based, 17 MCP tools
- **v2** (in progress): Headless direct control via Shizuku shell permissions + system-level APIs
- **v2-ROM** (planned): Custom AOSP ROM, ultimate solution

## Documentation

- `docs/DESIGN.md` — v1 architecture
- `docs/PLAN.md` — v1 implementation plan
- `docs/DESIGN-V2-HEADLESS.md` — v2 headless design
- `docs/PLAN-V2-HEADLESS.md` — v2 headless plan
- `docs/DESIGN-V2-ROM.md` — Custom ROM design
- `docs/PLAN-V2.md` — Custom ROM plan

## Tech Stack

- Kotlin 2.3 + Android SDK (minSdk 33, targetSdk 34)
- Jetpack Compose (Material Design 3) + Hilt DI
- Ktor Server (Netty) + MCP Kotlin SDK 0.8.3
- Shizuku (v2 shell permissions)
- Build: Gradle 8.14 (Kotlin DSL) + just (not make)

## Coding Conventions

- Define `interface`, implement with `Impl` suffix, bind via Hilt `@Binds`
- Package: `com.example.amctl`
- Coroutines: `viewModelScope` in ViewModel, custom `CoroutineScope` in Service
- Thread safety: `@Volatile` for `AccessibilityService.instance`
- Respond in Simplified Chinese

## Target Hardware

RhinoPi X1: Qualcomm QCS8550 (ARM64), 16GB LPDDR5X, Adreno 740 GPU
